			<h1>Cryptic Crosswords</h1>
			<p class="[ beta light italic ]">A <mark style="background-color: oklch(from currentColor l c h / 90%) !important; color: inherit !important;">Guide</mark> for <mark style="background-color: oklch(from currentColor l c h / 90%) !important; color: inherit !important;">Beginners</mark></p>
		</div>

		<div class="[ full-space ] [ flow ] ">
			<p>Cryptic crosswords can be <strong>intimidating</strong>.</p>
			<p>They seem like this completely <strong>indecipherable</strong> thing that <em>other</em> people do—people who use words like <strong>indecipherable</strong>.</p>
			<p>One thing that I think puts people off from trying out cryptic crosswords is a misunderstanding that cryptic crosswords are <em>complicated</em>, but I don’t think that's the case. Instead, I think cryptic crosswords are better described as being <em>complex</em>.</p>
			<p>What this means is that cryptic crosswords are not a tangled and broken thing with missing pieces that need to be assembled by pulling magic out of the aether; rather, they are a series of different types of knots which need to be recognised and undone.</p>
			<p>In other words, you will rarely need to have encyclopedic knowledge of a great many things to solve a crossword, and instead will go through a process of recognising different types of clues and performing some action with the clue based on what you have identified.</p>
			<p>You might even think of it like being presented with a series of math problems. It’s up to you to identify whether you will need to employ addition, subtraction, multiplication, etc. for each problem, and then perform that action. This process is very similar to solving crosswords.</p>
			<p>If you’ve ever worked out a riddle, played a word search game, or said a tongue-twister, then you’re already on your way to understanding how to do cryptic crosswords without even realising it.</p>
			<p>Now, I won’t sugarcoat it, getting your head around how cryptic crosswords work is not likely to come after a quick and straightforward learning session. It requires repetition and a breadth of exposure to different clues for things to start to click.</p>
